[Name] Tclap
[Summary] A small, flexible library that provides a simple interface for defining and accessing command line arguments.
[Description] TCLAP is a small, flexible library that provides a simple interface for defining and accessing command line arguments. It was intially inspired by the user friendly CLAP libary. The difference is that this library is templatized, so the argument class is type independent.
[License] MIT License
[Homepage] http://tclap.sourceforge.net
